# Local-Only Git Tracking for .kiro Directory
# 
# The .kiro directory contains AI-generated specs, steering rules, and task lists.
# We want to track these locally for version history but NOT push to the public repo.
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
#
# Option 1: Use git update-index (Recommended)
# After committing .kiro files locally, run:
#   git update-index --skip-worktree .kiro/
#
# This tells git to ignore changes to .kiro when pushing, but keeps local history.
#
# Option 2: Separate local branch
# Keep a local-only branch for .kiro files:
#   git checkout -b local-specs
#   git add .kiro/
#   git commit -m "Add local specs"
#   git checkout main
#
# Option 3: Git worktree
# Use a separate worktree for local-only files.
#
# CURRENT SETUP:
# The .gitignore excludes .kiro/ from being pushed to origin.
# To track locally, you can:
#   1. Remove .kiro/ from .gitignore temporarily
#   2. Commit the files
#   3. Add .kiro/ back to .gitignore
#   4. Run: git update-index --assume-unchanged .kiro/
#
# This gives you local version history without pushing to remote.
